{
  "analytics_identifier": null,
  "base_path": "/payroll-funding",
  "content_id": "75ed9f4b-9315-4557-bb1d-94fffba29bc6",
  "description": "Apply for financial help from HMRC if you cannot afford to fund an employee's tax refund",
  "details": {
    "department_analytics_profile": "",
    "external_related_links": [

    ],
    "introductory_paragraph": "<p>You can ask HM Revenue and Customs (<abbr title=\"HM Revenue and Customs\">HMRC</abbr>) for financial help if you need to give an employee a tax refund and cannot pay for it yourself.</p>\n\n<p>You need a Government Gateway user ID and password to apply. If you do not have a user ID, you can create one when you apply.</p>\n\n<p>If you’re an agent <a rel=\"external\" href=\"https://online.hmrc.gov.uk/shortforms/form/DMB_PAYE_EMP2\">use the email form instead</a>.</p>\n\n",
    "more_information": "<p>You normally take the amount of the refund off your next payment to <abbr title=\"HM Revenue and Customs\">HMRC</abbr>. You can reduce your payment of tax, National Insurance, Construction Industry Scheme (<abbr title=\"Construction Industry Scheme\">CIS</abbr>) deductions or student loan deductions.</p>\n\n<p>Apply for help if reducing your payment to <abbr title=\"HM Revenue and Customs\">HMRC</abbr> does not cover the tax refund.</p>\n\n<p>You should get the refund within 3 weeks if your application is successful. Most refunds are made within 7 to 10 days. You’ll get refunded faster if you provide your bank details.</p>\n\n<p>If you need to give more than one employee a tax refund, send a separate application for each.</p>\n\n<div role=\"note\" aria-label=\"Information\" class=\"application-notice info-notice\">\n<p>HMRC may reject your application if your payments are not up to date.</p>\n</div>\n\n",
    "other_ways_to_apply": "<h2 id=\"through-your-agent\">Through your agent</h2>\n\n<p>An agent can apply for you, but <abbr title=\"HM Revenue and Customs\">HMRC</abbr> can only contact them about your application if you’ve used <a href=\"/government/publications/tax-agents-and-advisers-authorising-your-agent-64-8\">Form 64-8</a> to authorise them.</p>\n\n",
    "start_button_text": "Start now",
    "transaction_start_link": "http://www.tax.service.gov.uk/digital-forms/form/Application-for-funding-a-tax-refund-for-an-employee/draft/guide",
    "variants": [

    ],
    "will_continue_on": "the HMRC website"
  },
